# k8s-app-chart CI/CD Agent Guide

## Repository Purpose
Generic, production-ready Helm chart for deploying frontend and backend services on Kubernetes. Supports external secrets, HPA, ingress, configmaps, and service accounts.

## Repository Structure
```
k8s-app-chart/
├── charts/
│   └── k8s-app-chart/        # Helm chart source
│       ├── Chart.yaml         # Chart metadata and version (bump this to release)
│       ├── values.yaml        # Default values
│       ├── .helmignore
│       └── templates/
│           ├── _helpers.tpl
│           ├── deployment.yaml
│           ├── service.yaml
│           ├── ingress.yaml
│           ├── configmap.yaml
│           ├── secret.yaml
│           ├── externalsecret.yaml
│           ├── hpa.yaml
│           └── serviceaccount.yaml
├── .github/
│   └── workflows/
│       └── release.yml        # chart-releaser GitHub Action
├── .agents                    # this file
├── .gitignore
├── README.md
└── DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md
```

## CI/CD Pipeline

### How Releases Work
1. Developer bumps `version` in `charts/k8s-app-chart/Chart.yaml` (SemVer)
2. Push to `main` branch
3. GitHub Action (`release.yml`) triggers on changes to `charts/**`
4. `helm/chart-releaser-action` detects the version bump, packages the chart
5. GitHub Release is created with the `.tgz` asset
6. `index.yaml` is updated on the `gh-pages` branch
7. Chart is available via Helm repo at `https://zeeemughal.github.io/k8s-app-chart`

### Versioning Rules (SemVer)
| Change Type     | Version Bump | Example         |
|-----------------|--------------|-----------------|
| Bug fix         | Patch        | 1.0.0 → 1.0.1  |
| New feature     | Minor        | 1.0.0 → 1.1.0  |
| Breaking change | Major        | 1.0.0 → 2.0.0  |

### To Release a New Version
1. Edit `charts/k8s-app-chart/Chart.yaml` — bump the `version` field
2. Commit: `git commit -m "chore: bump chart version to X.Y.Z"`
3. Push to `main` — the Action handles the rest

### Helm Repo
```bash
# Add repo
helm repo add zeeemughal https://zeeemughal.github.io/k8s-app-chart

# Install
helm install <release-name> zeeemughal/k8s-app-chart --version <X.Y.Z> -f values.yaml

# Upgrade
helm upgrade <release-name> zeeemughal/k8s-app-chart --version <X.Y.Z> -f values.yaml

# List versions
helm search repo zeeemughal/k8s-app-chart --versions
```

## GitHub Actions Workflow
- **File:** `.github/workflows/release.yml`
- **Trigger:** Push to `main` with changes under `charts/**`
- **Action:** `helm/chart-releaser-action@v1.6.0`
- **Pages branch:** `gh-pages`
- **Token:** Uses `GITHUB_TOKEN` (no extra secrets needed)

## Key Rules for Agents
- Never commit directly to `gh-pages` — it is managed by the chart-releaser Action
- Always bump `version` in `Chart.yaml` before expecting a new release
- Do not modify `appVersion` unless the application itself has a new version
- Keep chart name as `k8s-app-chart` — changing it breaks existing consumers
- Test chart rendering locally before pushing: `helm template . -f charts/k8s-app-chart/values.yaml`
